    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA166-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu celavuk kuṟippiṉāl (ET: kuṟippuṇarntu) vēṟupaṭṭa kiḻattikkut talaivaṉ colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE said to HER who had changed because of [his] intention of going.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA166">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            poṉṉu maṇiyum pōlum yāḻani</l>
<l>            ṉaṉṉar mēṉiyu nāṟiruṅ katuppum</l>
<l>            pōtum paṇaiyum pōlum yāḻaniṉ</l>
<l>            māta ruṇkaṇum vaṉappiṉ ṟōḷu</l>
<l>            mivaikāṇ ṭōṟu makamalinti yāṉu </l>
<l>            maṟanilai peṟṟō raṉaiyē ṉataṉṟalaip</l>
<l>            polantoṭip putalvaṉum poytal kaṟṟaṉaṉ</l>
<l>            viṉaiyum vēṟupulat tilaṉē niṉaiyiṉ</l>
<l>            yātaṉiṟ pirivā maṭantai</l>
<l>            kāta ṟāṉuṅ kaṭaliṉum peritē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent2">Like gold and sapphire your</l>
<l>good body and fragrant dark hair.</l>
<l rend="indent2">Like buds and bamboo your</l>
<l>beautiful kajal eyes and beautiful shoulder.</l>
<l>And I, rejoicing in [my] mind whenever seeing these,</l>
<l>am one of those who have obtained the state of virtue.</l>
<l rend="indent4">And, moreover,</l>
<l>[my] son with golden bracelets has [just] learned playing(?),<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">poytal</term>: here T.V.G.'s second instance of poy "to play", this time with weak conjugation (cf. NA 161.11).</note></l>
<l>and work is not for me in other places.</l>
<l rend="indent4">If I think [of it],</l>
<l>we will not separate for whatever reason, girl.</l>
<l>And love itself [is] greater than the sea.</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
